<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77fe44fd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460mmm–2"><num value="460mmm–2">§ 460mmm–2.</num><heading> McInnis Canyons National Conservation Area</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id77fe44fe-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460mmm–2/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is established the McInnis Canyons National Conservation Area in the State of Colorado and the State of Utah.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id77fe44ff-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460mmm–2/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Areas included</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Conservation Area shall consist of approximately 122,300 acres of public land as generally depicted on the Map.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id77fe4500-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/353/s4">Pub. L. 106–353, § 4</ref>, <date date="2000-10-24">Oct. 24, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1375">114 Stat. 1375</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/108/400/s1/c">Pub. L. 108–400, § 1(c)</ref>, <date date="2004-10-30">Oct. 30, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/2254">118 Stat. 2254</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id77fe4501-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
